                    <comment id="12784832" author="thetaphi" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2009 14:12:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached is the patch with javadocs and deprecation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will commit in a day.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12784840" author="thetaphi" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2009 14:18:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch with CHANGES.txt, thanks Shai!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12784842" author="thetaphi" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2009 14:20:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One addition: In my opinion, this class should be final. With the private ctor it gets automatically final (you cannot extend without ctor), but should we change this for now, too? This would be a (small) BW break.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12784845" author="shaie" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2009 14:22:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;if we&apos;re breaking BW, why not add the private ctor? I&apos;m sure that when 3.1 will be out, that won&apos;t be the only BW &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;20&quot; width=&quot;20&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;. Anyway, this is not a serious BW. If somebody relies on the ctor, then that somebody may also rely on the class not being final.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12784851" author="thetaphi" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2009 14:36:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think I keep this open for a moment, maybe others also have a comment about that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would also like to make it final and private (also the package private inner class).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12786983" author="thetaphi" created="Mon, 7 Dec 2009 16:50:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision: 887995. Thanks Shai!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
